  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Duties and responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Establish a cost analysis file for awarded projects once approved and activated</li></ul><ul><li>Check all purchase requisitions submitted by Project Engineers/Manager against the Budget; highlight discrepancies and get approval\nbefore issuance of POs by Procurement</li></ul><ul><li>Assist Project Managers with procurement and subcontracting issues </li></ul><ul><li>Assist in checking progress claims, variation claims, and subcontractor claims submitted by Project Managers</li></ul><ul><li>Evaluate and certify progress claims submitted by subcontractors, and discuss with management before the release of payment certificates to subcontractors</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor project costing and provide up-to-date report information on the project status</li></ul><ul><li>Lead monthly Project Sales Forecast meetings </li></ul><ul><li>Maintain the Project Sales Forecast file and ensure the input from the respective departments is in good order </li></ul><ul><li>Participate in project/operations reviews with Management whenever necessary </li></ul><ul><li>Monitor both retention receivable and payable and follow up as and when due</li></ul><ul><li>Liaison with all departments to ensure consistency in QS policy and procedures. </li></ul><ul><li>Participate and drive developments in ERP system implementation.</li></ul><ul><li>Other administrative duties.</li></ul><p><br />Requirement:</p><ul><li>Degree/Diploma in Quantity Surveying, Mechanical Engineering or related discipline  </li><li>Minimum of 3 to 4 years working experience in construction companies</li><li>Good written and verbal communication skills </li><li>Proficient in MSOffice, Especially MS Excel </li><li>Good team player and able to work under tight schedules and meet deadlines</li></ul>",
